Use "sudo ./install_service" to install the compiled VM as a linux server.
It will be installed to /usr/local/darjeeling, and a service script will be created in /etc/init.d/darjeeling.sh.


In order to compile darjeeling for 32-bit Galileo or Edison on a 64-bit platform
$ sudo apt-get install g++-4.8-multilib g++-multilib gcc-4.8-multilib gcc-multilib lib32gcc-4.8-dev
$ git clone https://github.com/intel-iot-devkit/mraa.git
$ mkdir build
$ cd build
$ export CFLAGS=-m32
$ export CXXFLAGS=-m32
$ cmake .. -DBUILDSWIGNODE=OFF -DBUILDSWIGPYTHON=OFF -DBUILDARCH=i386
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ gradle -b ../../build.gradle

To remove mraa:
$ sudo xargs rm < install_manifest.txt